Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/paradedb/paradedb/tree/dev/pg_search

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-search
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-search
Depends: postgresql-PGVERSION, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Full text search over SQL tables using the BM25 algorithm
  pg_search is a PostgreSQL extension that enables full text search over SQL tables using the BM25 algorithm,
  the state-of-the-art ranking function for full text search.
  It is built on top of Tantivy, the Rust-based alternative to Apache Lucene, using pgrx.
